cs.MM, cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SI, cs.CV

The paper deals with adaptive streaming, which is a multimedia delivery technique over the Internet. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.MM (Multimedia). The paper also considers network dynamics and user population characteristics, which suggests that it could belong to cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper proposes an optimization problem to maximize user satisfaction, which could fall under cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.SI (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed solution using simulations, which could also place it under cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) if the simulations involve video quality assessment.
